                       <p>I am a student at Centriq studying Full Stack Web Development! I want to pursue a career in this field because I got the mindset it takes to become a successful developer. I started out by working at Hy-Vee as a courtesy clerk at the grocery store. I was able to quickly move up and become a cashier within a few months of being there. After a few more months of being a cashier, I was asked to be a shift manager but denied the position because I was in school as a full-time student. As a cashier, I was trained at customer service because I took good care of our customers, and later got moved to the gas station.</p>
                       <p>While being at the gas station, there was usually not a manager on duty while I was working. I had to make manager-like decisions and make sure all duties were completed. The managers complimented me on always making sure I took good care of our customers. I was eager to learn more and wanted more for myself so I came to Centriq to start a career in Web Development.</p>
